The paper proposes a deep learning approach for histopathological malignancy diagnosis using convolutional neural networks. The focus is on image analysis and classification, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of deep residual neural networks and the case-based approach suggest that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper may also be relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories, as the authors mention the use of text-based information in their dataset.
